1
00:00:26,612 --> 00:00:35,395
[SPEAKER_00]: Hello, everyone, and welcome to Medford Happenings, a show for and about the city of Medford, and I am John Petrella.

2
00:00:36,155 --> 00:00:45,018
[SPEAKER_00]: And the purpose of this program is to give Medford citizens facts and information to help you make informed choices.

3
00:00:45,398 --> 00:00:56,042
[SPEAKER_00]: And today, I want to give a really warm welcome to Brianna Lungo Curran, mayor of the city of Medford,

4
00:00:57,525 --> 00:00:58,986
[SPEAKER_00]: Can't thank you enough for coming.

5
00:00:59,026 --> 00:01:01,207
[SPEAKER_00]: I know you're busy, so thank you so much.

6
00:01:01,307 --> 00:01:01,807
[SPEAKER_00]: Absolutely.

7
00:01:01,847 --> 00:01:02,447
[SPEAKER_00]: Happy to be here.

8
00:01:02,887 --> 00:01:03,288
[SPEAKER_00]: OK.

9
00:01:04,048 --> 00:01:06,709
[SPEAKER_00]: We're going to get right into it, Brianna, right into questions.

10
00:01:08,390 --> 00:01:12,811
[SPEAKER_00]: So most people know you as a city councilor.

11
00:01:13,332 --> 00:01:15,833
[SPEAKER_00]: They know you as the mayor of Medford.

12
00:01:17,733 --> 00:01:22,095
[SPEAKER_00]: But could you share a little bit more about yourself with our listeners?

13
00:01:22,155 --> 00:01:26,237
[SPEAKER_00]: Like, who is Brianna Lungo Kern?

14
00:01:27,486 --> 00:01:28,027
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you, John.

15
00:01:28,067 --> 00:01:28,867
[SPEAKER_01]: Thanks for having me.

16
00:01:28,887 --> 00:01:34,951
[SPEAKER_01]: I think I'll start with just saying I don't pretend to be somebody that I'm not.

17
00:01:34,971 --> 00:01:39,654
[SPEAKER_01]: I don't fight for things or do work because I feel like I have to.

18
00:01:39,674 --> 00:01:44,277
[SPEAKER_01]: I think what you see is what you get with me, and I really do believe in all the work we do.

19
00:01:44,297 --> 00:01:50,901
[SPEAKER_01]: I've been able to grow, whether that was a city councilor or now as mayor.

20
00:01:51,021 --> 00:01:55,443
[SPEAKER_01]: I am very thankful to the residents of Medford for giving me this opportunity since I was 21.

21
00:01:56,644 --> 00:01:59,146
[SPEAKER_01]: to grow in this role and really figure out who I was.

22
00:01:59,166 --> 00:02:07,173
[SPEAKER_01]: On top of being a mother of three, all of my kids have went through the Medford Public Schools.

23
00:02:07,734 --> 00:02:13,979
[SPEAKER_01]: My daughters are now in high school, but they went to the Roberts and the McGlynn schools.

24
00:02:14,019 --> 00:02:17,922
[SPEAKER_01]: My son's in sixth grade at the McGlynn Middle School.

25
00:02:19,283 --> 00:02:21,324
[SPEAKER_01]: And I also love to coach.

26
00:02:21,504 --> 00:02:25,206
[SPEAKER_01]: I started with girls basketball when my daughters were young.

27
00:02:25,966 --> 00:02:27,587
[SPEAKER_01]: I loved coaching.

28
00:02:27,627 --> 00:02:33,509
[SPEAKER_01]: I did it for about four or five years, and now I still am involved with Girls on the Run.

29
00:02:34,770 --> 00:02:57,448
[SPEAKER_01]: created my own boys program last year and the year before that did boys on the right track for for my son yep yep that's third through fifth graders so we still do girls on the run um starting up at the end of this month actually and i'll be a sub for for that organization love it um so i love to coach i run myself um i love to run races the last one i did was a half marathon and

