00:03:19,569 --> 00:03:21,430
[SPEAKER_01]: every second that I can.

38
00:03:22,371 --> 00:03:28,557
[SPEAKER_01]: I adore that little monkey, so that's what everybody's talking about and I almost couldn't believe it when I saw it on the world news a bunch of nights ago.

39
00:03:28,577 --> 00:03:35,443
[SPEAKER_01]: And I'm a hockey mom, I really enjoyed hockey and lacrosse and watching my kids play sports.

40
00:03:36,063 --> 00:03:42,452
[SPEAKER_01]: But I just want to try to be a humble person and a caring person and thoughtful in everything I do.

41
00:03:43,093 --> 00:03:44,555
[SPEAKER_01]: Not perfect by any means.

42
00:03:44,676 --> 00:03:44,996
[SPEAKER_01]: Right.

43
00:03:45,457 --> 00:03:46,078
[SPEAKER_01]: Nobody is.

44
00:03:46,418 --> 00:03:47,560
[SPEAKER_01]: No, nobody's perfect.

45
00:03:47,620 --> 00:03:51,285
[SPEAKER_01]: And I totally admit that I'm not one of those people, but I try to

46
00:03:51,986 --> 00:03:56,987
[SPEAKER_01]: make the best decisions I can, most of which I can never make everybody happy.

47
00:03:57,007 --> 00:04:01,409
[SPEAKER_01]: And I try to, but of course you never always can.

48
00:04:01,529 --> 00:04:04,710
[SPEAKER_01]: And sometimes I even second guess, did I make the right choice?

49
00:04:05,210 --> 00:04:15,613
[SPEAKER_01]: But when you're mayor, you're making hundreds of choices and decisions a week and responding to hundreds of thousands of emails.

50
00:04:15,753 --> 00:04:17,033
[SPEAKER_01]: So I do the best I can.

51
00:04:17,053 --> 00:04:19,854
[SPEAKER_01]: And I just try to stay true to who I am.

52
00:04:20,634 --> 00:04:22,255
[SPEAKER_01]: Live I always make the decisions.

53
